			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				There are times I am amazed at how much like real life this game is - well it is because there are real people behind the toons.  In  RL most people do what is accepted as &quot;right&quot; but what is &quot;right&quot; can change depending on what is accepted <img src="/images/faces/happy.gif" border=0 alt="happy.gif" height=16 hspace=0 width=18 vspace=0> .  In the game the Devs try to shape it to be a level playing field - some folks figure ways around that - I for one don't even try, not interested.   There are times when the bugs -the exploits - just screw up the whole fabric of the game.  As said by others, if you play the game for fun, there is no reason to use &quot;cheats&quot; - but then some folks must have a different idea of what fun is.
